erofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2867.topic"> Next Topic >> </a> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95% cellpadding=5 cellspacing=1><tr><td valign=top bgcolor=32323c class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Author</font></td><td valign=top bgcolor=32323c class=headings><font color=#FFFFFF>Comment</font></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umirdorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mirdorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 4:46:13 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I think they're pretty cool - so naturally I want to kill them.  <br><br>Has anyone solo'd them around level 43?  Especially as a bard?  I've tried single pulling once or twice, and haven't done well.  I'm sure it's a matter of positioning that I just haven't figured out yet.   <p>Mirdorr, 42 bard, Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucaeanthepaladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaeanthePaladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 4:58:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://caean.20fr.com/Caean2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> you can't solo pull at 43. But you're a bard, luckily you have tools to deal with multiples. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36323 ">Caean Sacroguerre, Knight of Tunare</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugiena.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 5:00:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I can hear the shouts now..<br><br>WHO TRAINED THE SPECS TO DOCKS?!?!?!?!<br><br>and TRAIN TO SRO!!<br><br>Need Rez by Specs plzkkthx!<br><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=88506"><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Giena Mountainstorm</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>Druid of the 53rd Corpse Run<br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://mywebpages.comcast.net/stonedogs/"> Stone Dog Clan </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> Ayonae Ro</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--><br><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> Utinam barbari spatium proprium tuum invadant</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugreystonethorngage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GreystoneThorngage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 5:12:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> will harmony work for single pulling them?<br> <p>Greystone Thorngage 39 Druid <BR>Bearer of the Stylish yet Affordable Dwarven Workboots <BR>Explorer of Luclin <BR>"Lo there do I see my father. Lo there do I see my mother, my sisters, and my brothers. Lo there do I see the line of my people, back to the beginning. Lo they do call me. They bid me take my place among them in the halls of Valhalla. Where the brave, may live forever"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/utydive.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tydive</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 5:16:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=4>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I have killed the Oasis Specs, mostly when I was in mid 30's.  I would pull all 8 to the south side of the lake and swarm kite em.  Worked fine.  They are OK exp and loot.  Some people love em, I think there are better places to solo mainly because the spawn is too slow and after my first pull the spawn is broken up too much.<br><br><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub118.ezboard.com/feqdivabardsofeverquestfrm55.showMessage?topicID=16.topic">How to kite guide</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br><br>1. Announce to zone what you are doing.<br>2. Use SoW pots so you can still keep up a 3 twist.<br>3. Apply your DE mask illusion prior to casting SoW, they last the same amount of time.<br>4. If you blow it and need to zone, announce train to SRo zone.  Don't go north.  Ever.<br><br>If this is your first try at swarm kiting, then go practice on fire beetles or something.  Do NOT try to learn this in a populated zone.  Work it all out with green mobs.  /redundancy off <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=146742>Tenter OneDrum</a><BR>Bard of the 48th Dirty Ditty<BR><a href=http://agema.8k.com>Agema</a> Companions of Ayonae Ro<BR><BR>Cogito cogito, ergo cogito sum. </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umirdorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mirdorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 5:16:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> Now, now.   Surely no one would mind if some crazy bard died a few times.<br><br>And since I'm so terrible at charming, what better way to get some dangerous practice on charming?  Heh.  <p>Mirdorr, 42 bard, Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/umirdorr.showPublicProfile?language=EN>mirdorr</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 5:18:41 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> Heh.  Don't worry, I'm not actually going to practice on the spectres. <p>Mirdorr, 42 bard, Ayonae Ro</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ucaeanthepaladin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>CaeanthePaladin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 6:05:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://caean.20fr.com/Caean2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I suggest killing the ones by the fear portal instead. It's in a newbie zone so the exp is better.<br><br>And no that doesn't have to mean the single spawn..just get an ivu (potions if need be) and get to the portal area. There's more than enough room in there to kite stuff around. You also have a very infrequently used zone line in the rathe mountains/ferrrooooottttt zone to train to if needed. <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=36323 ">Caean Sacroguerre, Knight of Tunare</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ualleaxravencrest.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Alleax Ravencrest</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 7:13:39 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I like killing them, as a Paladin I thoroughly enjoy dealing yummy death (again) to the undead (and am fairly equipped to do so) of any and all types. I can solo these IF they are already floating around as single mobs rather than a group. My harmonizing type spells do not seem to have much success as the few times I did try to do single pulls I got a trio or so of them angrily waving scythes at me in a menacing manner. I have yet to cross the water there to visit their Addams Family abode, is there anything of worth within that dwelling? <p>Alleax Ravencrest Paladin of the 41st TierKnight in the Order of Mithaniel Marr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugreystonethorngage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>GreystoneThorngage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Local Resident</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 7:25:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> Thoough i do not claim to be an expert, i beleive there is nothing but the specs up there. <p>Greystone Thorngage 39 Druid <BR>Bearer of the Stylish yet Affordable Dwarven Workboots <BR>Explorer of Luclin <BR>"Lo there do I see my father. Lo there do I see my mother, my sisters, and my brothers. Lo there do I see the line of my people, back to the beginning. Lo they do call me. They bid me take my place among them in the halls of Valhalla. Where the brave, may live forever"</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/usimondavid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Simondavid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 9:30:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=10>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I hunted these for about a lvl at 42. It is a slow spawn but gave me time to meditate. The first pull is the toughest because it is very hard to split them after that its a cakewalk. Make sure you announce what your doing the lower levels seem to freak out in shout and ooc if you dont.  Good Luck  <p>Simondavid 49 Barbarian Shaman Valiant Crusaders</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/urugalbloodwind.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Rugal Bloodwind</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Boardfellow</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/23/02 10:46:21 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=11>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> Who doesn't love them? Their smooth form, the seductive black robe that you just want to know what it hides, the sounds whispered in your ear as you are sliced apart..errr, wait, what was the question? Oh, killing them. No no, thats a vile nasty thing to do. But if you insist to try..you were given plenty good advice. Good luck. <p><p><font color="red">Baron Rugal Bloodwind<br><font color="6F6F6F">Slightly Insane Vampire Myrmidon<br><font color="maroon"><a href="http://kill-kill-kill.com">KILL</a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#383838><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub42.ezboard.com/ugarrathmoore.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garrath Moore</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Settler</span><br> <font color=#ff0000>(7/24/02 2:11:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2867.topic&index=12>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Who loves the Oasis spectres?</span><hr size=1> I love em...quadded em for a couple days...but the hills in Oasis were too annoying so I moved to TD...<br><br>AFAIK, there are nothing but spectres in that tower.  I pulled with my flux staff, so I really never got close enough to look.... <p>Garrath Moore <BR>Wizard of the 51st TL Request<BR>Officer, Divine Fate <BR>Ayonae Ro <BR></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub42.ezboard.com/fayonaerofrm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2867.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub42.ezboard.com/fa